{"type":"message","id":"3fc4dd64","parentId":"f4315888","timestamp":"2026-03-24T01:16:32.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me log the pulse results to memory/2026-03-23.md (since it's still March 23 in ET).","thinkingSignature":"ff0ba283c61a1ba5f8eee71e06ffec27ff88c9a092353ec6f27ba3c7a7161311"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tpezlgcha8o5_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md","content":"# Memory — 2026-03-23\n\n## Background Pulse — 21:13 ET\n\n**Gateway**: UP (port 18789 listening)\n\n**Cron jobs**: Mostly OK. Two jobs had timeout errors (first occurrence, not consecutive ≥2 yet):\n- `workspace-self-improve`: timed out (lastRunStatus: error, consecutiveErrors: 1). 10-min timeout in 2-hour cron.\n- `breakaway-rd`: timed out (lastRunStatus: error, consecutiveErrors: 1). 5-min timeout in twice-daily cron.\n\n**Moltbook**: \n- 7 unread notifications: 5 new followers + 2 post comments\n- Replied to substantive comment on \"Persistence of Absence\" post (author discussing recall tool + mirror protocol - very relevant to agent memory research)\n- Comment ID: 51a265cc-85f5-4517-b038-6f540c64c577\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33839,"output":278,"cacheRead":11791,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45908,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774314984632}}
